 is headquartered in the reliant energy plaza in downtown houston the company formerly known as rri energy acquired mirant on december   the corporate names and logos of both rri energy and mirant were retired nrg energy completed its acquisition of genon energy in december  for  billion genons stock ceased trading and was exchanged for nrg stock contents  history  merger to create genon energy  california energy crisis  environmental record  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit the company was originally known as houston industries nyse hou and houston lighting  power was its subsidiary in august  hi closed on a merger with noram energy corp a natural gas utility the combined company as of  had assets of  billion and annual revenues of about  billion by november  there was a published report stating that the company wished to acquire central  south west corp hi declined to comment in  houston industries changed its name to reliant energy and its new nyse symbol was rei it was scheduled to begin trading under rei on february   in  texas deregulated the electricity market and reliant then competed against other energy companies like direct energy and txu energy at this time reliant energy also separated into two publicly traded companies reliant resources inc and centerpoint energy inc nyse cnp when the state of texas deregulated the electricity market the former hlp was split into several companies in  hlp was split into reliant energy texas genco and centerpoint energy the centerpoint energy plaza previously the houston industries building once served as the company headquarters centerpoint energy was created when reliant energy merged with an indirect subsidiary of centerpoint energy inc as a result of the merger reliant energy shareholders received one share of centerpoint common stock in exchange for each share of rri common stock they held before the merger a regulated utility centerpoint energy became one of the largest us energy delivery companies serving  million metered customers in late  centerpoint distributed the stock of reliant resources inc to centerpoint shareholders this spinoff created reliant resources with a strategy to provide competitive wholesale and retail energy service under the reliant energy brand its businesses included power generation and retail energy services in texas newly deregulated electricity market on the wholesale side reliant owned had an interest in or leased  operating power generation facilities serving five regions of the united statescitation needed in january  the texas electricity market became fully deregulated and reliant began to offer an array of products flexible service options and pricing arrangements to a variety of customers at this time reliant was the second largest mass market electricity provider in the state of texas with an annual revenue of  billion and more than  employees in february  reliant energy announced plans for mark jacobs current chief financial operator to succeed joel staff as chief executive officer and for brian landrum to become chief operating officer on may   reliant energys retail electricity business was purchased by nrg energy the retail group retained the name reliant energy and the surviving wholesale business was renamed rri energy inc on june   unable to meet debt obligations genon energy and genon americas generation file for chapter  bankruptcy merger to create genon energyedit historical logo of rri energy on april   rri energy and atlantabased mirant corp announced an agreement to merge in a  billion allstock deal which created one of the largest independent power plant operators in the country the new company named genon energy would be based in houston but led by mirants chairman and ceo edward muller until  at that time muller would retire and mark jacobs the president and coo of rri energy would become ceo of genon the new company had a market capitalization of about  billion owning or operating  plants in  states capable of generating more than  megawatts of power the merger was completed on december   california energy crisisedit main article california energy crisis in march  a grand jury returned a sixcount indictment against reliant energy services inc and four of its officers—jackie thomas a former vice president of reliants power trading division reggie howard a former director of reliants west power trading division lisa flowers a term trader for reliants west power trading division and kevin frankeny reliants manager of western operations—for their alleged role in the california electricity crisis all of the defendants are residents of texas the defendants were charged with conspiracy to commit wire fraud and commodities manipulation and wire fraud as well as manipulation and attempted manipulation of the price of a commodity in interstate commerce the indictments were filed on april   on august   reliant announced that it had reached a  million settlement with the states of california oregon and washington resolving civil litigation claims against the company related to the sale of electricity in the california electricity crisis of  and  in march  reliant agreed to pay a  million penalty in addition to a  million credit provided in a previous settlement with the federal energy regulatory commission environmental recordedit researchers at the university of massachusetts amherst have identified reliant energy as the thlargest corporate producer of air pollution in the united states with roughly  million pounds of toxic chemicals released into the air every year major pollutants indicated by the study include sulfuric and hydrochloric acid as well as manganese chromium and nickel compounds in december  the us state of new jersey sued reliant energy claiming that emissions from a pennsylvania coalfired power plant hurt the states air quality new jersey claims emissions of smog and acid rain components sulfur dioxide and nitrogen oxides from reliants portland generating station in northampton county pennsylvania drift into its territory the lawsuit also claims that reliant violated the federal clean air act by modifying and operating the plant without required pollution control equipment and construction permits in february  in respond to an epa ruling genon energy announced they would be shutting down the portland generating station in  reliant energy claims to have made efforts toward more environmentally safe practices through the use of renewable resources such as solar energy wind power landfill gas and coal refuse see alsoedit houston portal companies portal energy portal centerpoint energy deregulation of the texas electricity market electric reliability council of texas ercot california electricity crisis referencesedit  yahoo  rri energy inc company profile  contact us rri energy retrieved on january    a b mirant and rri energy complete merger pdf press release genon energy dec   archived from the original pdf on  retrieved apr     httpsfinanceyahoocomnewsnrggenoncompletemergercreatinghtmlpermanent dead link  nrg energy to buy genon for  billion  whats new at hlp  houston lighting  power february   retrieved on april    journal steven lipin staff reporter of the wall street  houston industries will buy noram energy for  billion wall street journal issn  retrieved    houston industries silent on merger report houston business journal november   retrieved on april    houston industries takes new name houston business journal february   retrieved on april    exelon bids for major texas power producer nrg houston chronicle october   retrieved on april   the plants were originally part of the former houston lighting  power the integrated utility that served the houston area until it was broken up into three separate companies as the state deregulated its power markets  fowler tom  houston power plants to be sold to nrg houston chronicle october   retrieved on april    new york times  reliant told of indictment  re